  "measurement_note": "Size is E, the number of edges. The legal 8/32/128 tiers span 16x; each is a connected equal-weight graph built from a cycle plus distinct chords, so every edge is pseudo-critical. Weight-group contraction and one bridge traversal classify all edges in O(E log E) time. Correct exclude-and-force Kruskal testing takes O(E^2 alpha(V)), completes normally at E = 128, and is rejected by scaling.",
